# Documentation.
DescDetail: <<
  IO::Tokenized defines a bunch of functions allowing tokenized input
  from perl filehandles. In this alpha version tokens are specified by
  passing to the initialize_parsing function a list of token specifications.
  Each token specification is (a reference to) an array containing: the
  token name (a string), a regular expression defining the token and,
  optionally, an action function which calculates the value to be returned
  when a token matching the regexp is found.
<<
